<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="142" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,896,1102]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,896,922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Definition:</emphasis>
(amended from 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Soest, R. W. M." box="[468,653,896,923]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" pagination="1922" refId="ref7614" refString="Van Soest, R. W. M. (2002) Family Myxillidae Dendy, 1922. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 602 - 620. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 64" type="book chapter" year="2002">Van Soest, 2002</bibRefCitation>
, p. 619): 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dendy" authorityYear="1922" box="[760,883,896,922]" class="Demospongiae" family="Myxillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Myxillidae</taxonomicName>
with reticulate or plumoreticulate skeleton and a full complement of megascleres; microscleres include polydentate anchorate isochelae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,896,1102]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,968,994]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Remarks:</emphasis>
We amended the definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1904" box="[676,796,968,994]" class="Demospongiae" family="Myxillidae" genus="Stelodoryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[676,796,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Stelodoryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to allow for plumoreticulate skeletons within the genus to accommodate 
<taxonomicName authority="Lehnert &amp; Stone, 2020" authorityName="Lehnert &amp; Stone" authorityYear="2020" box="[348,586,1004,1030]" class="Demospongiae" family="Myxillidae" genus="Stelodoryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="jamesorri" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[348,586,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Stelodoryx jamesorri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,661,1004,1030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,661,1004,1030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The alternative of amending the genus would have been to erect a new genus for this species. We refrained from this option because the 
<typeStatus box="[941,989,1041,1067]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
material did not reveal enough DNA to strengthen this view by genetic data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
